CHOLERA - UGANDA
****************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Cholera - East Africa 971106225700
Cholera - East Africa (02) 971107232438
Cholera - East Africa: RFI 971110181857
Date: Sat, 10 Jan 1998 11:02:02 -0500
From: Jonathan Trouern-Trend <jtrend@erols.com>
Source: New Vision (Kampala, Uganda)

Up to 185 people were by yesterday known to have died of [cholera.
Fifty-three died in Mbale district alone. Ministry of Health records
indicated that 4,005 cases had been reported since the outbreak.
Health Minister Dr. Cyrispus Kiyonga said the cholera epidemic, which first
hit Kampala district over one month ago, had spread to 16 districts
exposing over 10 million people to the risk of infection.
Kiyonga also said schools should not re-open before their sanitation
facilities are properly assessed and cleared by district medical officers.
His comments were made during a meeting with district directors of medical
services and medical superintendents of hospitals from Mbale, Kapchorwa,
Kumi and Soroti districts.
